# ${PROJECT_NAME} Staging Runbook

Operator guide for the Hetzner Cloud staging environment provisioned by
`terraform/staging/`. Covers first-time setup, day-2 procedures (SSH/IP
rotation, Cloudflare flip), and the troubleshooting catalogue.

> Deploy + rollback procedures land in this runbook once unit-08 wires
> the GitHub Actions workflows. Until then, treat the deploy / rollback
> sections as pointers — they reference future workflows by filename.

---

## 1. Architecture overview

```
                ┌──────────────────────────────┐
                │ Cloudflare DNS (optional)    │
                │ app.staging.${CLOUDFLARE_ZONE}        │
                │ api.staging.${CLOUDFLARE_ZONE}        │
                └────────────┬─────────────────┘
                             │ A / AAAA
                             ▼
       ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
       │ Hetzner Cloud VM (${HETZNER_LOCATION} / ${HETZNER_SERVER_TYPE})         │
       │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐│
       │  │ Caddy (reverse proxy + ACME TLS)    ││
       │  └────────┬──────────────────┬─────────┘│
       │           │                  │          │
       │  ┌────────▼───────┐ ┌────────▼────────┐│
       │  │ api (HttpApi)  │ │ web (nginx+SPA) ││
       │  └────────┬───────┘ └─────────────────┘│
       │           │                             │
       │  ┌────────▼────────┐                    │
       │  │ db (postgres)   │                    │
       │  └─────────────────┘                    │
       │                                         │
       │  /etc/${PROJECT_NAME_LOWER}/{api,migrator}   ← secrets │
       │  /var/lib/${PROJECT_NAME_LOWER}/db           ← pg data │
       │  /var/lib/${PROJECT_NAME_LOWER}/.bootstrap-complete   │
       └─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

- **Terraform** (`terraform/staging/`) provisions the VM + firewall + sticky
  IPv4 + optional Cloudflare DNS records via the shared module
  `terraform/modules/${PROJECT_NAME}-env/`.
- **cloud-init** bootstraps the VM at first boot: installs Docker engine
  + compose plugin, creates the `deploy` user with scoped sudoers, lays
  down the load-bearing directory tree.
- **GitHub Actions** (lands in unit-08) deploys docker images from GHCR to
  the VM via SSH, then runs `docker compose up -d` against the rendered
  `docker-compose.yml` + `docker-compose.staging.yml` overlay.
- **State** lives in HCP Terraform workspace `${PROJECT_NAME_LOWER}-staging`
  (Execution Mode = Local).

