## 4. Deploy

When unit-08 lands, `gh workflow run staging-deploy.yml --repo
${GITHUB_OWNER}/${PROJECT_NAME_LOWER}` will deploy the latest `main` build to
the VM. Until then, the manual procedure is:

```bash
ssh -i ~/.ssh/${PROJECT_NAME_LOWER}_staging deploy@$(terraform output -raw vm_ipv4)
# on the VM:
cd /opt/${PROJECT_NAME_LOWER}     # operator-managed working dir
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.staging.yml pull
docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.staging.yml up -d
```

See unit-08's `staging-deploy.yml` for the canonical procedure once it
exists.

---

## 5. Rollback

unit-08 ships `staging-rollback.yml` for one-click per-service rollback.
Until then, the manual procedure is to flip the image tag in the
compose-overlay env vars and re-run `docker compose up -d`:

```bash
API_VERSION=v1.2.2 WEB_VERSION=v1.2.2 MIGRATOR_VERSION=v1.2.2 \
  docker compose -f docker-compose.yml -f docker-compose.staging.yml up -d
```

> Schema rollback is delicate: if the new release included migrations,
> rolling the API back without also rolling back the DB schema can fail.
> Confirm schema-compat before rolling back the migrator.

